  "title": "MANAGEMENT EXECUTIVE",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Support to HR team the end-to-end hiring process, posting job vacancy, arrange interview, managing employee onboarding. Update existing employee records, HR database.</li></ul><ul><li>Prepare employee letters, contracts, reports. Support workforce planning, manpower budgeting, optimization efforts. Serve as main contact for employee employment issues.</li></ul><ul><li>Support HR team to implement innovative HR strategies that support talent attraction, development, retention. Drive employee engagement initiatives to strengthen workplace culture, performance.</li></ul><ul><li>Manage employee relations, performance management. Conduct job analysis, forecasting to determine future staffing needs.</li></ul><ul><li>Organize meeting, assist planning company events. Oversee daily administrative tasks to maintain efficient office operations. Monitor office inventory, equipment, maintenance contracts and track company assets.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirement:</strong></p><ul><li>Qualified with working experience, preferably in relevant industry.</li><li>Willingness to learn and demonstrates a positive working attitude.</li><li>Well-groomed, hygienic, and presentable at all times.</li><li>Experience in beauty, healthcare, postpartum care sector.</li></ul>",
